The paper deals with the problem of online learning of optimal control for repeatedly operated systems in the presence of parametric uncertainty. This involves designing an agent that personalizes the control input to the plant taking into account the stochasticity involved. The paper uses machine learning techniques to solve this problem, which makes it likely to belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. Additionally, the paper deals with control systems, which makes it likely to belong to the cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-category. The paper also involves designing an agent that can learn from the environment, which makes it likely to belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. The paper also involves simulation of the system, which makes it likely to belong to the cs.RO (Robotics) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves designing an agent that can learn from the environment, which makes it likely to belong to the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category.
